        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 3:58PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Hartley to 6 miles south of
Albert Pike Recreation Area to near Glenwood. Movement was southeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Umpire, Athens, Muddy Fork, and Burg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
